## What does it mean? How and when can I use it?

### In a nutshell...

...composition is the placement or arrangement of visual elements in a work of art. It is how things in a work are organised and put together! It is defined as

> the nature of something's ingredients or constituents; the way in which a whole or mixture is made up.

In the case of art history, we are dealing with pictorial images when talking about composition. We often talk about how different images are "composed." It means what in the picture has been placed where?
